<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="977" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d977">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512337 Shipping/11–2344</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4684</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-23">November 23,
                                1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department refers to the Embassy’s
                            despatch no. 7879 of September 13, 1944 concerning the exemption from
                            taxation of the revenues obtained in Cuba by vessels owned by or
                            chartered to the War Shipping Administration.</p>
                        <p>Now that the new administration has assumed office, the Department is of
                            the opinion that the Embassy should press for a prompt <pb facs="1011" n="997" xml:id="pg_997"/> and definite reply to its representations
                            on this subject as originally presented to the Cuban Government in note
                            no. 731 of October 15, 1942.<note n="49" xml:id="d977fn49">Not
                                printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>G[<hi rend="smallcaps">reen</hi>] H. H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ackworth</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>